        "heading_JKgaCG": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "How to choose a pear cut promise ring",
            "heading_tag": "h1"
          }
        },
        "richtext_gAWgmz": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Choosing the right pear cut promise ring comes down to personal style and how the ring will be worn.</p><p><strong>If you prefer something minimal</strong></p><p>A solitaire pear cut ring keeps the focus on the shape itself and offers a clean, elegant look.</p><p><strong>If you want something more distinctive</strong></p><p>Look for designs with multiple stones or a <a href=\"https://thepromiseco.com/collections/toi-et-moi-promise-rings\" title=\"https://thepromiseco.com/collections/toi-et-moi-promise-rings\">Toi et Moi style</a>, which adds a more expressive and modern feel.</p><p><strong>If everyday wear matters</strong></p><p>Choose a balanced setting that protects the pointed tip while remaining comfortable to wear daily.The best choice is always the one that feels natural and meaningful to the person wearing it.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
